@pedrodyl: The cage is better than [Nihil Spellbomb](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nihil Spellbomb) because it can also stop [Birthing Pod](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Birthing Pod) and [Green Sun’s Zenith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Green Sun’s Zenith).


@Axelle: I have to agree with you. The best blue zombies don’t come into play from the graveyard, they just exile cards from the graveyard, and the cage does nothing to prevent that from happening.


@Swords\_to\_exile and @Snafinturtle: There are a lot of cards that allow you to cast spells from your library, I don’t know where you guys are getting two and four respectively. Besides the four that were mentioned, [Spellshift](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spellshift) can be used to cast a spell out of your library, [Panglacial Wurm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Panglacial Wurm) can be cast from the library, and all of the cards with “Ripple” ([Surging Flame](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Surging Flame)) can cast cards from your library.

@LPFan55 and @Chmur: In the current standard, there’s [Galvanoth](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Galvanoth) and [Garruk’s Horde](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Garruk’s Horde) that can cast cards from ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
